AVG Anti-virus says the keygen contains the Trojan "Generic 16.CIPF" whatever that is.  The installation file for the program itself is virus free.  I ran the keygen in a virtual machine and it does generate correct key information.  If you have virtualization, take a snapshot, run the keygen,  copy the key, and restore the snapshot.
